    70	  qaly_per_death_averted:
    71	    remaining_life_expectancy: {dist: normal, mean: 26, sd: 4, min: 5, unit: years}
    72	    utility_weight: {dist: triangular, low: 0.60, mode: 0.78, high: 0.92, unit: utility_weight}
    73	    source: >-
    74	      Populations in the causal mortality studies are low-income adults roughly
    75	      age 50-64. Remaining life expectancy ~26y is calibrated to
    76	      [Chetty et al. (2016, JAMA)](https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jama/fullarticle/2513561):
    77	      bottom-income-quartile life expectancy at 40 is ~78 (men) to ~83 (women),
    78	      implying mid-20s remaining years around age 55. Utility ~0.78 is
    79	      calibrated to US EQ-5D population norms (e.g.,
    80	      [Jiang et al. 2021](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11136-020-02650-y),
    81	      ages 55-64 ~0.80 overall, lower at low income). Discounted at 3% with a
    82	      half-cycle correction.
