    98	      Table 3: VQALY for 2026 impacts at a 3% discount rate, low/central/high
    99	      $339k / $726k / $1,105k in constant 2025 dollars. Inflated to the May
   100	      2026 price level with [CPI-U](https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/CPIAUCNS)
   101	      335.123 / 321.943 (2025 annual average) = 1.0409: $353k / $756k / $1,150k.
   102	      One series, one price level, denominated at the 3% reference rate; at
   103	      other rates the model rescales by the adult PV-QALY ratio (vqaly_adult
   104	      below), which reproduces HHS Table 2's discounted PV QALYs (19.5 at 3%,
   105	      11.7 at 7%) to within 0.1%, keeping the benefit/cost ratio consistent
   106	      with the discount slider.
