codex
The first substantive discrepancies are emerging in the manuscript’s labels rather than the arithmetic: the “RCT-only” endpoint retains 1% credibility for every non-randomized tier, and its surviving randomized bucket is collaborative mental-health care—not the lottery bucket named in the prose. I’m quantifying those effects and checking the reported ratios and decompositions before assigning severity.
